          ],
          "series_items": [],
          "patch_summary": "This patch limits the number of iterations in the shrink_delalloc function to prevent it from blocking indefinitely when dealing with large amounts of writeback data. The function now iterates over delalloc work in units of 128MiB, rather than trying to reclaim all available space at once. This change aims to strike a balance between making progress on space reclaim and avoiding arbitrarily long syscall latencies.",
