              "message_id": "b1da881707fe4a7010c4b4543aafbee26fb70a45.1775756790.git.boris@bur.io",
              "url": "https://lore.kernel.org/all/b1da881707fe4a7010c4b4543aafbee26fb70a45.1775756790.git.boris@bur.io/",
              "subject": "[PATCH v4 2/4] btrfs: account for compression in delalloc extent reservation",
              "date": "2026-04-09T17:49:08Z"
            }
          ],
          "series_items": [],
          "patch_summary": "This patch addresses an issue in the Btrfs file system where delayed reference reservations were under-estimated due to compression. When compression is enabled, the maximum extent size is reduced from 128MiB to 128KiB, leading to a significant discrepancy between estimated and actual extents. The patch introduces a new function `btrfs_inode_max_extents` to calculate the correct number of extents based on the inode's properties and the maximum extent size. This change ensures that reservations are accurately calculated even when compression is enabled, preventing under-reservation of delayed reference reservations for delalloc writes.",
          "analysis_source": "llm-chunked-no-replies",
          "review_comments": [],
          "list_id": "linux-btrfs@vger.kernel.org"
        },
