              "version": 4,
              "message_id": "05bde74e587402f5d77897f0507a292ab9522355.1775756789.git.boris@bur.io",
              "url": "https://lore.kernel.org/all/05bde74e587402f5d77897f0507a292ab9522355.1775756789.git.boris@bur.io/",
              "subject": "[PATCH v4 1/4] btrfs: reserve space for delayed_refs in delalloc",
              "date": "2026-04-09T17:49:06Z"
            }
          ],
          "series_items": [],
          "patch_summary": "This patch addresses a problem in the Btrfs file system where space is not reserved for delayed references (delayed_refs) during delalloc operations. Delalloc uses a per-inode block reservation to anticipate metadata needs, but this calculation does not account for delayed refs. As a result, when writeback occurs and delayed refs are generated, they draw from an under-reserved trans_handle's delayed_refs_rsv, leading to incorrect assessments of reserved space in the metadata space reclaim logic. The patch aims to fix this issue by reserving space for delayed refs during delalloc operations.",
